ce:section.ce:para:
To illustrate the sensing ability of PECDs towards Hg2+, fluorometric titration experiments were conducted. As shown in Fig. 5
                        A, upon the addition of different amounts of Hg2+ into 10 μL PECDs ABS, the fluorescent intensity gradually decreased along with increasing the concentration of Hg2+ from 0.1 to 100 μM. The calibration curve for determining Hg2+ was obtained by plotting the values of F/F0 versus the concentrations of Hg2+ (Fig. 5B). The correlation coefficients (R2) were calculated as 0.997 and 0.9926 within the two linear concentration ranges of 0.1−10 and 10−100 μM, respectively (see the SI, Figs. S2 and S3). The limit of detection (LOD) was estimated to be 75 nM based on a signal-to-noise ratio of 3 at three times the standard deviation of 3 measurements of blank samples. This result explicitly demonstrated the excellent sensitivity of PECDs to Hg2+ by comparing to those obtained from other CDs or nanomaterials based Hg2+ chemosensors reported previously (Table 1
                        ).
